1. Top Performing Regions and Countries(Geographical Analysis):¶

In [5]:
grouped_data = df.groupby(['Region', 'Country']).agg({'Total Revenue': 'sum', 'Total Profit': 'sum'}).reset_index()

# Calculate total revenue and profit for each region
region_totals = grouped_data.groupby('Region').agg({'Total Revenue': 'sum','Total Profit': 'sum'})

# Calculate total revenue and profit for each country
country_totals = grouped_data.groupby('Country').agg({'Total Revenue': 'sum', 'Total Profit': 'sum'})

# Identify top performing regions and countries based on total revenue and profit
top_regions = region_totals.nlargest(10, 'Total Revenue')
top_countries = country_totals.nlargest(10, 'Total Revenue')

print("Top Performing Regions:")
print(top_regions)

print("\nTop Performing Countries:")
print(top_countries)

5. Seasonal Trends Analysis:¶

In [11]:
# Extract month and year from order dates
df['Order Month'] = df['Order Date'].dt.month
df['Order Year'] = df['Order Date'].dt.year

# Group by overall_month and aggregate overall_Total_revenue
monthly_revenue = df.groupby('Order Month')['Total Revenue'].sum()
print(monthly_revenue)
# Plot seasonal trends
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
monthly_revenue.plot(kind='line', marker='o',color='darkred')
plt.title('Seasonal Trends in Sales')
plt.xlabel('Month')
plt.ylabel('Revenue')
plt.xticks(range(1, 13), ['Jan', 'Feb', 'Mar', 'Apr', 'May', 'Jun', 'Jul', 'Aug', 'Sep', 'Oct', 'Nov', 'Dec'])
plt.grid(True)
plt.legend()
plt.show()

In [12]:
# Group by month and aggregate Total_revenue of Each Year
monthly_revenue = df.groupby(['Order Year', 'Order Month'])['Total Revenue'].sum().reset_index()

# Plot seasonal trends
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
for year in monthly_revenue['Order Year'].unique():
    data = monthly_revenue[monthly_revenue['Order Year'] == year]
    plt.plot(data['Order Month'], data['Total Revenue'], marker='o', label=year)

plt.title('Seasonal Trends in Sales')
plt.xlabel('Month')
plt.ylabel('Revenue')
plt.xticks(range(1, 13), ['Jan', 'Feb', 'Mar', 'Apr', 'May', 'Jun', 'Jul', 'Aug', 'Sep', 'Oct', 'Nov', 'Dec'])
plt.legend()
plt.grid(True)
plt.show()

6. Calculate the profit margin for each item type¶

In [13]:
#  Calculate profit margin
df['Profit Margin%'] = (df['Unit Price'] - df['Unit Cost']) / df['Unit Price'] * 100

# Sort DataFrame by profit margin
df = df.sort_values(by='Profit Margin%', ascending=False)
df
# # Plot profit margin for each item type
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.bar(df['Item Type'], df['Profit Margin%'], color='skyblue')
plt.title('Profit Margin by Item Type')
plt.xlabel('Item Type')
plt.ylabel('Profit Margin (%)')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.grid(axis='y', linestyle='--', alpha=0.8)
